         <abstract>
            <p>A digital music system capable of synthesizing a modest sized orchestra has been implemented in our laboratory. This paper discusses several aspects of the software for controlling sound generation. Sound generation is viewed as a cooperative effort between two or more processes. One process controls data input from floppy disk and the real time periphery. One or more processes service the synthesizer hardware to control envelope generation. A language for interconnecting the synthesizer hardware and organizing the software is presented.</p>
         </abstract>
